The paper discusses cyber-security analysis in power system state estimation, which involves the use of information and communication technology (ICT) to monitor and control the smart power grid. This topic falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also mentions the use of graph-based frameworks for security analysis, which involves the use of algorithms and data structures (cs.IT) and potentially artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper discusses the potential applications of graph-based security analysis in the smart power grid, which involves the use of networking and internet technologies (cs.NI).
